  <section class="faq" id="faq" aria-labelledby="faq-title">
    <div class="faq-inner">
      <p class="section-kicker">06 / FAQ</p>
      <h2 id="faq-title" class="faq-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="reveal">
          <summary>What is Sonura?</summary>
          <p>Sonura is a music production studio. Describe what you want and get professional-quality beats, loops, vocals, and full tracks in seconds. Export stems, iterate endlessly, and use everything commercially.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="reveal" data-reveal-delay="0.03s">
          <summary>Is Sonura free to use?</summary>
          <p>Yes. You get free credits to start creating immediately. No credit card required. Create beats, loops, and tracks at full quality before choosing a plan.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="reveal" data-reveal-delay="0.06s">
          <summary>Can I monetize the music I create?</summary>
          <p>Everything you create with Sonura is yours with full commercial rights. Release on Spotify, sell as beats, use in client work, score a film. No royalty splits, no attribution required.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="reveal" data-reveal-delay="0.09s">
          <summary>Will platforms de-rank my music if I use AI tools?</summary>
          <p>Sonura is for those crafting original arrangements and sound, not replacing the human decisions that make a track yours.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="reveal" data-reveal-delay="0.12s">
          <summary>What genres does Sonura support?</summary>
          <p>Virtually every genre: trap, house, techno, pop, rock, jazz, lo-fi, drill, R&B, country, ambient, cinematic, and more. Sonura understands sub-genres and specific style descriptors so you get exactly the sound you're after.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="reveal" data-reveal-delay="0.18s">
          <summary>Do I need production experience?</summary>
          <p>No. Sonura works for complete beginners and professional producers alike. If you can describe what you want, you can create it. No DAW knowledge or music theory required, though it integrates seamlessly if you have them.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="reveal" data-reveal-delay="0.24s">
          <summary>How fast is creation?</summary>
          <p>Under 10 seconds on average. Loops in 5–8 seconds, full tracks in 8–12 seconds. No queues, no rendering delays.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="reveal" data-reveal-delay="0.3s">
          <summary>Can I export stems for my DAW?</summary>
          <p>Yes. Export individual stems (drums, bass, melody, FX, vocals) or the full mix, ready to drop into Ableton, FL Studio, Logic, Reaper, Pro Tools, and any DAW.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="reveal" data-reveal-delay="0.32s">
          <summary>Does the plugin work in my DAW?</summary>
          <p>Almost certainly. The free Sonura Flow plugin runs right inside Ableton Live, Logic Pro, FL Studio, Reaper, Studio One, Bitwig, Cubase, GarageBand, and any other VST3 or AU host, on Mac and Windows.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="reveal" data-reveal-delay="0.36s">
          <summary>How is Sonura different from sample packs?</summary>
          <p>Sample packs are pre-made and shared across thousands of producers. Sonura creates completely original audio tailored to your exact specifications. Every creation is unique and matched to your vision.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="reveal" data-reveal-delay="0.42s">
          <summary>What makes Sonura different from other AI music tools?</summary>
          <p>Sonura is built for producers, not just listeners. You get stem exports, multi-track layering, real-time iteration, full commercial rights, and studio-grade output, all in one platform. Most AI music tools create a finished song you can't edit. Sonura gives you the building blocks.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

